Yesterday's research into PETA was cut short by sad news but I wanted to share this rabbit hole I've discovered and follow it down some more
Firstly thanks to @EMOANAKlN @arcwhite @UncladLad @RagingMango_ for your replies I have checked sources for you and followed the money trail
Yes PETA does euthanize animals; to end the suffering of that animal. I fully support this.
In 12 years the PETA shelter has euthanized 31,250 animals. The animal agriculture industry has just killed that many animals in 6 seconds.
The Center for Consumer Freedom is a front group funded by Philip Morris Outback Steakhouse KFC cattle ranchers etc https://t.co/vLOx6bzpCw
Nathan J. Winograd (that HuffPost article) is the Director of the No Kill Advocacy Center and is linked to the Center for Consumer Freedom
PETA Has Spayed and Neutered Nearly 100,000 Companion Animals (Including Feral Cats and Pit Bulls) in Free and Low-Cost Clinics
You get the idea. This website https://t.co/s6CjCQgGig is VERY in depth and one of the only reliable sources I've found so far. Still going.
And please please please even if you don't want to properly research PETA euthanasia properly please just watch this https://t.co/aRgriUHsUs
@dnmstrategic haha ahhh damn sorry dude :) i guess it's what kind of pushed me towards supporting PETA a bit, but yea soz :P
Anyway that's all for euthanasia. Still researching and following the rabbit hole. There's so much industry backed misinformation out there.
@dnmstrategic I was surprised too. Happy to have reached at least one person tonight. I think maybe I pissed a lot of people off lol oops
